Grid-search

julia> nlvdis = [15; 25] ; metric = [:mah]
1-element Vector{Symbol}:

  50
 100

(nlvdis = Any[15, 25, 15, 25, 15, 25, 15, 25, 15, 25  …  15, 25, 15, 25, 15, 25, 15, 25, 15, 25], metric = Any[:mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah  …  :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah, :mah], h = Any[1.0, 1.0, 2.0, 2.0, 4.0, 4.0, 6.0, 6.0, Inf, Inf  …  1.0, 1.0, 2.0, 2.0, 4.0, 4.0, 6.0, 6.0, Inf, Inf], k = Any[30, 30, 30, 30, 30, 30, 30, 30, 30, 30  …  100, 100, 100, 100, 100, 100, 100, 100, 100, 100])

Final prediction (Test) using the optimal model

julia> model = lwplsrda(nlvdis = res.nlvdis[u], metric = res.metric[u], h = res.h[u], 
           k = res.k[u], nlv = res.nlv[u])
Jchemo.JchemoModel{typeof(lwplsrda), Base.Pairs{Symbol, Any, NTuple{5, Symbol}, @NamedTuple{nlvdis::Int64, metric::Symbol, h::Float64, k::Int64, nlv::Int64}}}(Jchemo.lwplsrda, nothing, Base.Pairs{Symbol, Any, NTuple{5, Symbol}, @NamedTuple{nlvdis::Int64, metric::Symbol, h::Float64, k::Int64, nlv::Int64}}(:nlvdis => 15, :metric => :mah, :h => 1.0, :k => 30, :nlv => 1))

julia> fit!(model, Xtrain, ytrain)
